{
  "stem": "11964.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was another very traumatic experience.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember worrying about what my sisters would think, where was I, what my landlady would think, what had happened to me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Finally, I was able to find my way back to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't remember what other question you asked me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the idea of liberation-- let me return to that-- was really a bittersweet feeling.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was good to know that we don't have to hide any longer.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was very sad and very painful to know we have no place and nobody to come to.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But one of the very strangest feelings that I personally had is that I somehow or other could not summon a feeling of vengeance or revenge.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I did not feel that I must go and find the first German and kill him or her.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was just totally, totally imbued by the sorrow of losing our parents, by being a non-person, being in no man's land, not having a place to return to, not having anything or anybody to look forward to or to look for.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And being totally disconnected and uprooted at such an early age, I really didn't know what I called life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I really didn't know whether just pure existence without fear of whether or not I would be able to survive, whether that is going to be my life, or whether or not I would be able to make something of myself.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I really didn't think about any possibilities.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I just thought of, now, what is going to happen?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How am I going to find myself in this turmoil of a world?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What's going to happen to Poland?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What's going to happen to me?",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
